Announcement: Realigning with Our Open-Source Mission

We need to directly address recent statements made in internal discussions that significantly conflict with our core values and mission. Specifically, it was incorrectly suggested that our community should position itself as a vendor selling proprietary AI solutions to corporate clients, pitch pilot projects aimed at securing commercial business, conceal our methodologies to maintain competitive advantages, and emphasize monetization over community-driven upskilling.

To clarify explicitly:
â€¢ We are not building proprietary, closed, or commercial products. Our agents, methods, prompts, and technology will remain fully open-source, transparent, and reproducibleâ€”aligned strictly with MIT's open research values.
â€¢ We do not aim to replace human roles or prioritize efficiency over learning. Our mission is rooted in human-in-the-loop AI development, focused on education, empowerment, and democratizing AI knowledge.
â€¢ We reject any elitist mindset. Our community welcomes and values participation from everyone, never positioning ourselves as an exclusive elite group.
â€¢ We are explicitly non-commercial. While we collaborate with industry partners for educational support, sponsorship, and practical feedback, we are not selling services, proprietary technology, or consultancy projects.

Moving forward, our upcoming keynote will further emphasize these values, addressing any lingering confusion. We appreciate your continued support in upholding our open-source, inclusive, and academically-driven mission.
